{{Cleanup|date=February 2011}} {{Infobox Convention |name = Gitex |status = Active |genre = [[Technology]][[Consumer Electronics]][[Telecommunications]] |venue = Dubai World Trade Center |location = [[Dubai, United Arab Emirates]] |first = 1996 |attendance = 150,000 |organizer = Dubai World Trade Center |website = {{URL|http://www.gitex.com/}} }}
'''GITEX''' ("'''Gulf Information Technology Exhibition'''") is an annual consumer computer and electronics [[trade show]], exhibition, and conference that takes place in [[Dubai]], [[United Arab Emirates]] at the Dubai World Trade Centre. Its exhibitions in the Middle East have attracted numerous participants, most notably in 2009 when Microsoft released Windows 7 with 150,019 people present.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gitex|url=http://www.tutorgigpedia.com/ed/GITEX|publisher=TutorGig Encyclopedia|accessdate=14 March 2013}}</ref>
The GITEX Shopper & Consumer Electronics Expo attracts ICT retailers and suppliers such as [[Gateway TechnoLabs|Gateway Group]], 50 Cent, [[Etisalat]], [[Red Hat|RedHat]], and [[Dell]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.itnewsafrica.com/2012/10/business-booms-as-gitex-technology-week-2012-ends/|title=Business Booms As GITEX Technology Week 2012 Ends|last=Wakama|first=Abby|date=October 19, 2012|newspaper=It's News Africa}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ameinfo.com/-red-hat-exhibits-dell-gitex-315622|title=Red Hat exhibits with Dell at Gitex 2012|last=Mesbah|first=Rana|date=October 17, 2012|newspaper=AME Info|accessdate=14 March 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121018221719/http://www.ameinfo.com/-red-hat-exhibits-dell-gitex-315622|archivedate=18 October 2012|deadurl=yes|df=}}</ref> The consumer participants include [[IT professionals]], technology enthusiasts, students and consumers as well as regional traders.
==GITEX history== The show was launched in 1981 as GITE and occupied Hall One of the [[Dubai World Trade Centre]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dwtc.com/|title=Dubai World Trade Centre Official Website|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>. With the launch of MacWorld at the 1988 show, GITEX (the X had been added by now) expanded to two halls of the exhibition centre. For some years it has now filled the entire DWTC complex, currently consisting of 10 exhibition halls comprising a million feet of exhibition space.
GITEX Shopper 2009 had 150,019 visitors representing 121 nationalities.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}
The 2012 event included 60% from Middle East, 19% from Africa, 13% from the Americas, 4% from East and South Asia and 4% from Europe. There was a 24% increase from Africa as compared to 2011.<ref>{{cite news |last=Alshoaiby |first=Mohammed |title=Africa set to become ICT investment destination |url=http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentid=20121017139848 |accessdate=14 March 2013 |newspaper=Saudi Gazette |date=October 17, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121104103528/http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/index.cfm?method=home.regcon&contentid=20121017139848 |archivedate=4 November 2012 |df= }}</ref>
== GITEX Cairo == GITEX Cairo was launched in 1998 and ran for three years before the 2002 edition was postponed.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://gulfnews.com/news/gulf/uae/general/gitex-cairo-postponed-1.380035|title = Gulf News|last = |first = |date = March 5, 2002|work = |accessdate = September 2014}}</ref>
== GITEX News == GITEX 2018 (38th Technology Week) was held during OCT 14 – 18, 2018 at [[Dubai World Trade Centre]]. The Department of [[Sharjah]] eGovernment had previously announced that 36 government departments in the [[Emirate]] would be taking part in the GITEX Technology Week 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tahawultech.com/industry/government/sharjah-egov-major-participation-gitex/|title=Sharjah announces major participation at GITEX|last=|first=|date=|work=|access-date=}}</ref>
GITEX 2016 which marked the 36th year of GITEX was held on 16th-20th October.<ref>http://www.malloftheemirates.com/blog/lifestyle/gitex-technology-week-2016</ref> The focus was on cutting-edge technology - Robotics and drones.
