'''Nutriset''' is the French manufacturer and trademark owner of [[Plumpy'nut]], the [[peanut]]-based [[food]] for use in [[famine relief]]. It was formulated in 1997 by [[André Briend]], a [[France|French]] pediatric nutritionist.<ref name=rice>{{cite news |author=Rice, Andrew |coauthors= |title=The Peanut Solution |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/09/05/magazine/05Plumpy-t.html?_r=1&hp |quote=Plumpy’nut is also a brand name, however, the registered trademark of Nutriset, a private French company that first manufactured and marketed the paste. ...|work=[[New York Times Magazine]] |date=September 2, 2010 |accessdate=2010-09-02 }}</ref> The majority of Plumpy'nut is produced in a Nutriset factory in [[Malaunay]], and [[Unicef]] purchases 90 percent of the supply from that factory for [[humanitarian aid]].<ref name=rice/>
