'''Sijelo''' (In [[Ijekavian]]), '''silo''' (In [[Ikavian]]) or '''selo''' (In [[Ekavian]]) is the name of an evening gathering at a house, a social event (i.e. a [[party]]), in [[former Yugoslavia]]. The use of the word ''sijelo'' is particularly widespread in [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]].

