{{Infobox Newspaper |name = [[Image:Smederevska Sedmica logo.jpg|225px|Smederevska Sedmica]] |image = Smederevska Sedmica No 259.jpg |image_size = 225px |caption = Cover of Smederevska Sedmica No 259 with [[Alexander, Crown Prince of Yugoslavia|Alexander II Karađorđević]] during his first visit to Smederevo, May 25, 2003. |type = Local Independent Media |format = A4 |foundation = 2 September 1997 |ceased publication = 15 July 2005 |price = |owners = Milan Petrović |publisher = EUROPRESS, Smederevo |editor = Miroslav Đorđević |language =[[Serbian language|Serbian]] |political = |circulation = |headquarters = [[Smederevo]], [[Serbia]] |ISSN = |website = }}
'''''Smederevska Sedmica''''' ([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Serbian Cyrillic]]: Смедеревска Седмица) was an independent local magazine in [[Serbia]], published weekly between September 1997 and July 2005. It was the only magazine in Smederevo that was independent during the rule of [[Slobodan Milošević]].<ref>[http://www.vazdan.com/link_search.php?criteria=Nezavisne%20novine vazdan :: Linkovi :: Pretraga<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.knight-international.org/i/braithwaite.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-08-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929090909/http://www.knight-international.org/i/braithwaite.pdf |archivedate=2007-09-29 |df= }}</ref> The magazine slogan was ''Truth at least once a week'' ([[Serbian Cyrillic alphabet|Serbian Cyrillic]]: Истина бар једном седмично). The word "sedmica" means "seven" in Serbian, but it can also mean a "week".
As the magazine editorial says "Smederevska sedmica was published by staff dedicated to freedom of speech and of the media despite the fact that they operate in a difficult economic and political environment".
